"Use the following functions to set and control the Flex layout on any "
"parent Widget."
msgstr "Si usano le seguenti funzioni per impostare e controllare il layout Flex su qualsiasi Widget genitore."

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:51
msgid ""
"The parent Widget must be a Flex container for these styles to take "
"effect. The functions below cause the parent Widget to become a Flex "
"container if it is not already."
msgstr "Affinché questi stili abbiano effetto, il Widget genitore deve essere un contenitore Flex. Le funzioni seguenti fanno sì che il Widget genitore diventi un contenitore Flex, se non lo è già."

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:59
msgid "Flex flow"
msgstr "Flusso Flex"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:61
msgid ":cpp:expr:`lv_obj_set_flex_flow(widget, flex_flow)`"
msgstr ":cpp:expr:`lv_obj_set_flex_flow(widget, flex_flow)`"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:63
msgid "The possible values for ``flex_flow`` are:"
msgstr "I possibili valori per ``flex_flow`` sono:"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:65
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_ROW`: Place the children in a row without "
"wrapping"
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_ROW`: Posiziona gli elementi figlio in una riga senza riavvolgimento"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:66
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_COLUMN`: Place the children in a column "
"without wrapping"
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_COLUMN`: Posiziona gli elementi figlio in una colonna senza riavvolgimento"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:67
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_ROW_WRAP`: Place the children in a row with"
" wrapping"
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_ROW_WRAP`: Posiziona gli elementi figlio in una riga con riavvolgimento"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:68
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_COLUMN_WRAP`: Place the children in a "
"column with wrapping"
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_COLUMN_WRAP`: Posiziona gli elementi figlio in una colonna con riavvolgimento"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:69
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_ROW_REVERSE`: Place the children in a row "
"without wrapping but in reversed order"
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_ROW_REVERSE`: Posiziona gli elementi figlio in una riga senza riavvolgimento ma in ordine inverso"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:70
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_COLUMN_REVERSE`: Place the children in a "
"column without wrapping but in reversed order"
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_COLUMN_REVERSE`: Posiziona gli elementi figlio in una colonna senza riavvolgimento ma in ordine inverso"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:71
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_ROW_WRAP_REVERSE`: Place the children in a "
"row with wrapping but in reversed order"
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_ROW_WRAP_REVERSE`: Posiziona gli elementi figlio in una riga con riavvolgimento ma in ordine inverso"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:72
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_COLUMN_WRAP_REVERSE`: Place the children in"
" a column with wrapping but in reversed order"
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_COLUMN_WRAP_REVERSE`: Posiziona gli elementi figlio in una colonna con riavvolgimento ma in ordine inverso"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:74
msgid ""
"These values cause the Widget's layout behavior to model `CSS Flexbox`_ "
"behavior by combining flex-direction_ and flex-wrap_ as defined under "
"flex-flow_."
msgstr "Questi valori fanno sì che il comportamento del layout del Widget modelli il comportamento di `CSS Flexbox`_ combinando flex-direction_ e flex-wrap_ come definito in flex-flow_."

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:82
msgid "Flex align"
msgstr "Allineamento Flex"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:84
msgid ""
"To manage placement of children use "
":cpp:expr:`lv_obj_set_flex_align(widget,  main_place, cross_place, "
"track_cross_place)` which makes the parent Widget model the Flex-"
"container behavior defined `here <justify-content_>`_."
msgstr "Per gestire il posizionamento degli elementi figlio, si usa :cpp:expr:`lv_obj_set_flex_align(widget,  main_place, cross_place, track_cross_place)` che fa sì che il modello del widget padre imposti il comportamento del contenitore Flex definito `qui <justify-content_>`_."

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:89
msgid ""
"``main_place`` determines how to distribute the items in their track on "
"the main axis. E.g. flush the items to the right on "
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_ROW_WRAP`. (It's called justify-content_ in"
" CSS.)"
msgstr "``main_place`` determina come distribuire gli elementi nella loro track sull'asse principale. Ad esempio, allinea gli elementi a destra su :cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_FLOW_ROW_WRAP`. (In CSS si chiama justify-content_.)"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:93
msgid ""
"``cross_place`` determines how to distribute the items in their track on "
"the cross axis. E.g. if the items have different height, align them "
"against the bottom of the track. (It's called align-items_ in CSS.)"
msgstr "``cross_place`` determina come distribuire gli elementi nella loro track sull'asse trasversale. Ad esempio, se gli elementi hanno altezze diverse, li allinea alla parte inferiore della track. (In CSS si chiama align-items_.)"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:96
msgid ""
"``track_cross_place`` determines how to distribute the tracks (It's "
"called align-content_ in CSS.)"
msgstr "``track_cross_place`` determina come distribuire le track (in CSS si chiama align-content_.)"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:99
msgid "The possible values are:"
msgstr "I valori possibili sono:"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:101
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_ALIGN_START`: means left when direction is "
"horizontal, top when vertical (default)"
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_ALIGN_START`: indica sinistra quando la direzione è orizzontale, in alto quando è verticale (il default)"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:102
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_ALIGN_END`: means right when direction is "
"horizontal, bottom when vertical"
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_ALIGN_END`: indica destra quando la direzione è orizzontale, in basso quando è verticale"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:103
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_ALIGN_CENTER`: simply center with respect to "
"direction"
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_ALIGN_CENTER`: semplicemente centra rispetto alla direzione"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:104
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_ALIGN_SPACE_EVENLY`: items are distributed so "
"that the spacing between any two items (and the space to the edges) is "
"equal. Does not apply to ``track_cross_place``."
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_ALIGN_SPACE_EVENLY`: gli elementi vengono distribuiti in modo che la spaziatura tra due elementi qualsiasi (e lo spazio tra i bordi) sia uguale. Non si applica a ``track_cross_place``."

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/common-widget-features/layouts/flex.rst:107
msgid ""
":cpp:enumerator:`LV_FLEX_ALIGN_SPACE_AROUND`: items are evenly "
"distributed in the track with equal space around them. Note that visually"
" the spaces are not equal since all the items have equal space on both "
"sides.  This makes the space between items double the space between edge "
"items and the container's edge.  Does not apply to ``track_cross_place``."
