"found from ``lvgl/script/LVGLImage.py``."
msgstr "The RLE algorithm is a simple compression algorithm that is based on the fact that for many adjacent pixels, the color is the same.  The algorithm simply counts how many repeated pixels with the same color there are, and stores the count value and the color value.  If the up-coming pixels are not repeated, it stores the non-repeat count value and original color values.  For more details, the script used to compress the image can be found from ``lvgl/script/LVGLImage.py``."

