" are provided, LVGL's display handling works like \"traditional\" double "
"buffering.  This means the :ref:`flush_callback` callback only has to "
"update the address of the frame buffer to the ``px_map`` parameter."
msgstr ":cpp:enumerator:`LV_DISPLAY_RENDER_MODE_FULL` The buffer size(s) must match the size of the display.  LVGL will always redraw the whole screen even if only 1 pixel has been changed.  If two display-sized draw buffers are provided, LVGL's display handling works like \"traditional\" double buffering.  This means the :ref:`flush_callback` callback only has to update the address of the frame buffer to the ``px_map`` parameter."

