"screen, the display buffer is 800x480 = 375k pixels. If there are 4 "
"tiles, the ideal tile size is approximately 93k pixels. Based on this, "
"core utilization is as follows:"
msgstr "The ideal tile size is calculated as ``ideal_tile_size = draw_buf_size / tile_cnt``. For example, in :cpp:enumerator:`LV_DISPLAY_RENDER_MODE_DIRECT` mode on an 800x480 screen, the display buffer is 800x480 = 375k pixels. If there are 4 tiles, the ideal tile size is approximately 93k pixels. Based on this, core utilization is as follows:"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/main-modules/display/tiling.rst:36
msgid "30k pixels: 1 core"
msgstr "30k pixels: 1 core"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/main-modules/display/tiling.rst:37
msgid "90k pixels: 1 core"
msgstr "90k pixels: 1 core"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/main-modules/display/tiling.rst:38
msgid "95k pixels: 2 cores (above 93k pixels, 2 cores are used)"
msgstr "95k pixels: 2 cores (above 93k pixels, 2 cores are used)"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/main-modules/display/tiling.rst:39
msgid "150k pixels: 2 cores"
msgstr "150k pixels: 2 cores"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/main-modules/display/tiling.rst:40
msgid "200k pixels: 3 cores (above 186k pixels, 3 cores are used)"
msgstr "200k pixels: 3 cores (above 186k pixels, 3 cores are used)"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/main-modules/display/tiling.rst:41
msgid "300k pixels: 4 cores (above 279k pixels, 4 cores are used)"
msgstr "300k pixels: 4 cores (above 279k pixels, 4 cores are used)"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/main-modules/display/tiling.rst:42
msgid "375k pixels: 4 cores"
msgstr "375k pixels: 4 cores"

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/main-modules/display/tiling.rst:44
msgid ""
"In :cpp:enumerator:`LV_DISPLAY_RENDER_MODE_DIRECT`, the screen-sized draw"
" buffer is divided by the tile count to determine the ideal tile sizes. "
"If smaller areas are refreshed, it may result in fewer cores being used."
msgstr "In :cpp:enumerator:`LV_DISPLAY_RENDER_MODE_DIRECT`, the screen-sized draw buffer is divided by the tile count to determine the ideal tile sizes. If smaller areas are refreshed, it may result in fewer cores being used."

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/main-modules/display/tiling.rst:48
msgid ""
"In :cpp:enumerator:`LV_DISPLAY_RENDER_MODE_FULL`, the maximum number of "
"tiles is always created when the entire screen is refreshed."
msgstr "In :cpp:enumerator:`LV_DISPLAY_RENDER_MODE_FULL`, the maximum number of tiles is always created when the entire screen is refreshed."

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/main-modules/display/tiling.rst:51
msgid ""
"In :cpp:enumerator:`LV_DISPLAY_RENDER_MODE_PARTIAL`, the partial buffer "
"is divided into tiles. For example, if the draw buffer is 1/10th the size"
" of the screen and there are 2 tiles, then 1/20th + 1/20th of the screen "
"area will be rendered at once."
msgstr "In :cpp:enumerator:`LV_DISPLAY_RENDER_MODE_PARTIAL`, the partial buffer is divided into tiles. For example, if the draw buffer is 1/10th the size of the screen and there are 2 tiles, then 1/20th + 1/20th of the screen area will be rendered at once."

#: ../../../lvgl/docs/intermediate/details/main-modules/display/tiling.rst:55
msgid ""
"Tiled rendering only affects the rendering process, and the "
":ref:`flush_callback` is called once for each invalidated area. "
"Therefore, tiling is not visible from the flushing point of view."
msgstr "Tiled rendering only affects the rendering process, and the :ref:`flush_callback` is called once for each invalidated area. Therefore, tiling is not visible from the flushing point of view."

